item.title: Help my please... portforwarding teamviewer
item.dc:creator: @ApocalypseX ApocalypseX
item.description:
@ApocalypseX wrote:

[quote=“pure 0wnz1, post:3, topic:398472”][quote author=XD you k0 XD link=topic=495608.msg3623382#msg3623382 date=1307639071]
Well go to starter menu search for Cmd
then search ipconfig
go to internet put in ur ip most ppl : (192.168.1.1)
then the name is probly admin and password to
if not ask the owner of the pc bout name and password, then go to advaced settings press portforwarding then put ur ip in then UCP and TCP just do both then do 43594 - 43594 then at comment use runescape
now press add
then mark it and use apply and run ur server now ur portforwarded but dont froget to press enable port forwarding on ur router settings.

No problem
[/quote]

thats the problem idk what mij pass is :S[/quote]
Most cases are:
user: Admin pass: Admin
user: Administrator pass: Administrator
user: Admin pass: 1234
user: (Router Name) Pass: Admin
Try those. Or just think about anything I didn’t mention; it’s most likely easy.
And SAY what type of router you have.
